{"name":"fds","version":"1.0.2","description":"Set file descriptors to non-blocking","main":"index.js","scripts":{"test":"echo \"Error: no test specified\" && exit 1","install":"node-gyp rebuild"},"repository":"https://github.com/terinjokes/libuv-fd-open","keywords":["libuv","fd"],"files":["index.js","src","binding.gyp"],"license":"MIT","homepage":"https://github.com/terinjokes/libuv-fd-open","dependencies":{"bindings":"^1.2.1","nan":"^2.0.5"},"gypfile":true,"gitHead":"6fffd5161b457d0db65b67f454b71035b57183c9","versions":[{"number":"1.0.0","date":"2015-03-31T01:57:31.592Z"},{"number":"1.0.1","date":"2015-08-26T18:13:42.924Z"},{"number":"1.0.2","date":"2016-04-11T00:26:52.753Z"}],"readme":"# fds\n> Set non-block mode on file descriptors.\n\n## Why?\n\nPart of the API contract for [libuv](https://github.com/libuv/libuv) specifies that file descriptors should already be in non-blocking mode.\nNewer versions of libuv set the non-blocking flag, and thus node version that utilize them have the fix. Unfortunately 0.10 and the early versions of 0.12 do not.\n\nThis is a simple backport of libuv code packaged up into a module that can be utilized everywhere.\n\n## Usage\n\n```javascript\nvar http = require('http');\nvar fds = require('fds');\n\nfds.nonblock(3)\n\nhttp.createServer(function(req, res) {\n  res.writeHead(200, {\n    'Content-Type': 'text/plain'\n  });\n  res.end('Hello World\\n');\n}).listen({\n  fd: 3\n});\n```\n","created":"2015-03-31T01:57:31.592Z","modified":"2016-04-11T00:26:52.753Z","lastPublisher":{"name":"terinjokes","email":"terinjokes@gmail.com"},"owners":[{"name":"terinjokes","email":"terinjokes@gmail.com"}],"other":{"_attachments":{},"_from":".","_id":"fds","_nodeVersion":"4.3.0","_npmOperationalInternal":{"host":"packages-12-west.internal.npmjs.com","tmp":"tmp/fds-1.0.2.tgz_1460334410701_0.11552270618267357"},"_npmUser":{"name":"terinjokes","email":"terinjokes@gmail.com"},"_npmVersion":"2.14.17","_rev":"1-482a29376d46105094ff0de2bc247397","_shasum"